This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine translation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new architecture for sequence to sequence learning using convolutional neural networks. Additionally, since the architecture involves convolutional layers, it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of gated linear units and attention modules suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as well. Finally, since the paper proposes a new approach to sequence to sequence learning, it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
